This paper is about improving saliency in convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new method for improving saliency using Green's function convolution, which involves modifying the architecture of the neural network (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of the method and compares it to other approaches, which involves experimentation and analysis (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves training neural networks, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves processing images, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
